
[1]distributive

   DISTRIBUTIVE, a.

   1. That distributes; that divides and assigns in portions; that deals
   to each his proper share; as distributive justice.

   2. That assigns the various species of a general term.

   3. That separates or divides; as a distributive adjective.

     DISTRIBUTIVE, n. In grammar, a word that divides or distributes, as
   each and every, which represent the individuals of a collective number
                                as separate.
